1.title: Bringing Down the House
1.plot: After Bobo's ex-girlfriend Daina sweet-talks an old codger into letting the team hunt in his uncle's cabin, Dustin, D'Roy, Kacey, Bobo and Daina rev up their 8x8s and travel through bayous, swamps, rivers and woods to get to the island where the old cabin sits. After digging up a whole lot of junk (and complaining about his ex-girlfriend tagging along on the hunt), Bobo finds a trap door in the kitchen floor containing whiskey bottles, a sawed off shotgun and an antique dynamite plunger, leading the gang to believe this homeowner may have been up to no good. But ...

2.title: One Man's Trash Is Another Man's Treasure
2.plot: Dustin, D'Roy, Kacey and Bobo are having a great time at their favorite bar but are shocked to learn that their bar tabs are so big they've been cut off. The owner agrees to wipe out their debt if they can bring her some valuable vintage items. Dustin arranges to hunt an unused landfill and then borrows a very expensive piece of equipment to help get the job done. They fire up the side-by-sides and race to the dig site only to crash into a ditch. When they discover more booby traps along the way, the gang suspects something sinister is going on. When they finally ...

3.title: Union Jacked
3.plot: In an effort to collect some Civil War relics, Dustin and the gang head out to find a campsite where an historic Confederate gunboat sank. There's just one problem -- a logjam that's been stopping up the river for decades. Once the guys are able to reach some higher ground, all they can find are discarded cans of beer and other duds. Yet after a serious scare, the gang manages to dig up an antique powder horn, an officer's gun and a bugle, but that's only part of the battle. Now Dustin and D'Roy have to see if their found items will be major moneymakers at D'Roy's ...

4.title: Chamber Potluck
4.plot: Cousin Chris thinks he has spotted a ghost and decides to search for the treasure of a long lost pirate, while the rest of the gang heads out to hunt at an old abandoned dairy farm. Soon a group of rival relic hunters are hot on their trail, but Dustin, D'Roy, Kacey and Bobo manage to lose them as they finally arrive at the dig site. It's a relic hunter's paradise as they find a bounty of valuable items, including an antique camera, some coins and a pair of old horn shears. The guys think they are in for a huge payday until their rivals show up again and threaten to ...

5.title: Anchor Management
5.plot: Since the water level along the East Pearl River is at an extraordinarily low point, Dustin, D'Roy, Kacey, Bobo and Daina decide to hunt on an old sandbar that was once deep under the water in hopes of finding some real pirate treasure. After uncovering a ton of junk, they eventually find a treasure that's worth their while. The item is larger than most, causing half of the team to go back to Dustin's house to build a bayou barge so they can float it down the river. Now left to their own devices, Daina and Bobo are forced to stay back and guard the treasure, but with ...

6.title: Monster Baiter
6.plot: The Taylors camp out and search for buried treasure on Honey Island, where cousin Chris goes questing for the fabled Honey Island Swamp Monster.

1.title: Pot Luck
1.plot: D'Roy and Dustin are relic hunters in Louisiana's huge Honey Island Swamp. Working with their extended family, the father-and-son team searches for lost treasures left behind by pirates, gangsters, and militiamen. And when they find something worth selling, they head to the local antique dealers, collectors, and pawnshops to hawk their goods.

2.title: Honey Island Pirates
2.plot: Dustin and D'Roy go on the hunt for long-lost relics left behind by the swamp's most infamous pirate, Jean Lafitte, more than 500 years ago. Knives, guns, swords, or even pirate gold could be buried in the swamp, but a deal with the landowner means the clock is ticking and a unwelcome visit from a family foe could threaten to shut the whole thing down. Can the Taylor clan fend him off to unearth the pirate booty? Or will they go home empty-handed?

3.title: Spoils of War
3.plot: D'Roy strikes the deal of a lifetime getting the Taylors access to one of the swamps most infamous secrets: a former World War II POW camp that once housed captured Nazis. Antique weapons and valuable military artifacts may be buried in the ground, but when an unexpected visitor shows up, will D'Roy's arrangement turn out to be a deal with the Devil?

imdb.plot outline: SWAMP HUNTERS follows the Taylor clan, a group of burly, loud and proud rednecks, who hunt for relics in the swamps around their home in Southern Mississippi. Their swampy hunting grounds are loaded with valuable finds from the days of the pirates, the civil war, and voodoo ceremonies, and each episode finds the Taylors braving snakes, boars, gators and rival relic hunters in the quest for historic finds that could land them big money.
